---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SwimWorkout from "../components/SwimWorkout.tsx";
const title = "Lap Lab — stanwood.dev";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={title}
  description="Generate custom swim workouts for any duration, pace, and skill level. Sets, drills, and intervals built around your goals — just pick a time and hit the pool."
  slug="swim"
  favicon="/favicon-swim.svg"
  themeColor="#0d9488"
  schemaCategory="HealthApplication"
  schemaName="Lap Lab"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif;
        background-color: #f5f0eb;
        color: rgb(15 23 42);
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
      }

      /* ── Fade-in animation for workout generation ── */
      @keyframes fadeIn {
        from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(12px); }
        to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
      }
      .animate-fadeIn {
        animation: fadeIn 0.4s ease-out;
      }

      /* ── Hero section ── */
      .hero-container {
        position: relative;
        width: 100%;
        height: 280px;
        overflow: hidden;
        border-radius: 1.25rem;
        margin-top: 1rem;
      }
      @media (min-width: 640px) {
        .hero-container {
          height: 340px;
        }
      }
      .hero-image {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
        display: block;
      }
      .hero-overlay {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background: linear-gradient(
          to bottom,
          rgba(245, 240, 235, 0) 0%,
          rgba(245, 240, 235, 0) 40%,
          rgba(245, 240, 235, 0.6) 70%,
          rgba(245, 240, 235, 1) 100%
        );
        pointer-events: none;
      }
      .hero-title-overlay {
        position: absolute;
        bottom: 0;
        left: 0;
        right: 0;
        padding: 2rem 1.5rem 1.25rem;
        pointer-events: none;
      }

      /* ── Pool-themed accent bar ── */
      .lane-divider {
        height: 4px;
        background: repeating-linear-gradient(
          90deg,
          #0d9488 0px,
          #0d9488 20px,
          #f5f0eb 20px,
          #f5f0eb 28px,
          #e11d48 28px,
          #e11d48 48px,
          #f5f0eb 48px,
          #f5f0eb 56px
        );
        border-radius: 2px;
      }

      /* ── Sandstone card surface ── */
      .card-sandstone {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
        backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
        -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
        border: 1px solid rgba(13, 148, 136, 0.1);
        border-radius: 1.25rem;
      }

      /* ── Print styles: clean single-page PDF ── */
      @media print {
        /* Hide everything except the print workout */
        body > * { display: none !important; }
        body { background: white !important; margin: 0 !important; padding: 0 !important; }

        .print-workout {
          display: block !important;
          position: fixed;
          top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
          padding: 32px 40px !important;
          max-width: 100% !important;
          font-size: 11pt;
        }

        /* Prevent page breaks inside sections */
        .print-workout > div { break-inside: avoid; }

        @page {
          size: letter;
          margin: 0.5in;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </Fragment>

  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-nav">Skip to content</a>

  <!-- Subtle lane divider at very top -->
  <div class="lane-divider"></div>

  <main id="main-content" class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 pt-8 pb-24 print:hidden">
    <!-- Nav -->
    <div class="flex items-center">
      <a href="/" class="retro-back">&larr; stanwood.dev</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero Image -->
    <div class="hero-container">
      <img
        src="/images/lap-lab.webp"
        alt="Aerial view of a turquoise swimming pool with lane dividers"
        class="hero-image"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        width="1280"
        height="720"
      />
      <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
      <div class="hero-title-overlay">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-11 h-11 rounded-xl bg-teal-600/90 backdrop-blur-sm shadow-lg shadow-teal-900/20">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 15a4 4 0 004 4h9a5 5 0 10-.1-9.999 5.002 5.002 0 10-9.78 2.096A4.001 4.001 0 003 15z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900">
              Lap Lab
            </h1>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Header copy -->
    <header class="mt-3">
      <p class="text-teal-700/60 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wider">swim workout generator</p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
        Pick your duration, pace, and pool type. We'll build you a workout with a warmup, main set, and cooldown.
        Don't love it? Shuffle until you do.
      </p>

      <!-- Pace reference guide -->
      <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl border border-teal-100 bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm p-4">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-400 mb-3">Pace guide — per 100</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2 text-center text-xs">
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-amber-50 border border-amber-100 p-2.5">
            <div class="font-bold text-amber-800 text-sm">2:00 – 2:30</div>
            <div class="text-amber-700 mt-0.5">Casual / Fitness</div>
            <div class="text-stone-400 mt-1 leading-tight">Recreational lap swimmer</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-teal-50 border border-teal-100 p-2.5">
            <div class="font-bold text-teal-800 text-sm">1:35 – 1:55</div>
            <div class="text-teal-700 mt-0.5">Intermediate</div>
            <div class="text-stone-400 mt-1 leading-tight">Regular training, masters</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-sky-50 border border-sky-100 p-2.5">
            <div class="font-bold text-sky-800 text-sm">1:10 – 1:30</div>
            <div class="text-sky-700 mt-0.5">Competitive</div>
            <div class="text-stone-400 mt-1 leading-tight">Club / collegiate speed</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[11px] text-stone-400 leading-relaxed">
          Yards pools (SCY) run slightly faster — subtract ~5 sec from your meters pace to start.
          Some workouts include a pull buoy, kickboard, or fins — bring them if you have them.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Lane divider decoration -->
      <div class="lane-divider mt-5"></div>
    </header>

    <!-- How it's built -->
    <section class="mt-8 space-y-4">
      <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-400">How workouts are structured</p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-100 bg-amber-50/60 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-amber-500/90 text-white text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-0.5">Warmup</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">Easy continuous swim to raise your heart rate. Usually 200–600m of freestyle or choice. No rest intervals — just move.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-orange-100 bg-orange-50/60 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-orange-500/90 text-white text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-0.5">Pre-Set</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">Drills and technique work before the main set. Kickboard, pull buoy, IM rotations — activates all four strokes and locks in your form.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-teal-100 bg-teal-50/70 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-teal-600 text-white text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-0.5">Main Set</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">The meat of the workout. Reps on an interval, or long sustained efforts — depends on your focus. Endurance = longer distances. Speed = shorter bursts with rest.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-cyan-100 bg-cyan-50/60 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-cyan-500/90 text-white text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2.5 py-0.5">Cooldown</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">Easy swim to flush out lactic acid. Usually backstroke or choice at a relaxed pace. Finishes the total distance and brings your heart rate down.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Equipment callout -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white/50 backdrop-blur-sm p-4">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-400 mb-3">Equipment you might need</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 text-xs text-center">
          <div>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 px-2.5 py-1 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px]">Pull</span>
            <p class="mt-1.5 text-stone-500 leading-tight">Pull buoy between your thighs — isolates arms, removes the kick.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-800 px-2.5 py-1 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px]">Kick</span>
            <p class="mt-1.5 text-stone-500 leading-tight">Kickboard held out front — isolates legs, builds kick strength.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full bg-sky-100 text-sky-800 px-2.5 py-1 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px]">Fins</span>
            <p class="mt-1.5 text-stone-500 leading-tight">Swim fins — more propulsion, good for butterfly and fast sprints.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[11px] text-stone-400">None of these are required — workouts are generated with what you have. Skip equipment sets or substitute an easy freestyle if you don't have them.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lane-divider"></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Decode the lingo -->
    <section class="mt-8" aria-label="Glossary of swim workout terms">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-400">Decode the lingo</p>
        <span class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-teal-600/70">cheat sheet</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Generated workouts use shorthand. Here's what each term means when it shows up in your set.
      </p>

      <!-- Set shapes -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-teal-100 bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm p-4 mb-3">
        <p class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-teal-700/70 mb-3">Set shapes — how reps progress</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-4 gap-y-2.5 text-xs">
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Descend</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Each rep faster than the last. "Descend 1–4" = four reps, fastest is the last.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Build</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Start easy and accelerate <em>within</em> a single swim. By the wall, you're at top speed.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Negative split</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Second half faster than the first half of the same swim.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Ladder</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Distances climb (50, 100, 150…) then often drop back down.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Pyramid</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Up and back down — 50, 100, 150, 100, 50. Same total, builds and tapers.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Broken swim</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">A long swim chopped with brief rests. Lets you hold faster pace than nonstop.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Odds &amp; evens</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Alternating effort — odd reps hard, even reps easy (or vice versa).</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Race pace</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">What you'd hold in an actual race — hard but controlled, not all-out.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Effort levels -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-100 bg-amber-50/40 backdrop-blur-sm p-4 mb-3">
        <p class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-700/70 mb-3">Effort levels — how hard to push</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-4 gap-y-2.5 text-xs">
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-amber-900 min-w-[88px]">Easy</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Conversational. You could chat between breaths. ~60% effort.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-amber-900 min-w-[88px]">Moderate</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Working but smooth. Could hold this for a long set. ~75%.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-amber-900 min-w-[88px]">Threshold</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">"T-pace" or "red line" — comfortably hard, just below all-out. ~85%.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-amber-900 min-w-[88px]">Sprint</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Maximum effort, short distances. Full rest between reps. 100%.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Drills -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-sky-100 bg-sky-50/40 backdrop-blur-sm p-4 mb-3">
        <p class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-700/70 mb-3">Drills — technique tune-ups</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-4 gap-y-2.5 text-xs">
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-sky-900 min-w-[110px]">Catch-up</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Touch your hands at the front before pulling — forces a long, clean stroke.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-sky-900 min-w-[110px]">Fingertip drag</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Drag your fingertips on the water during recovery. Builds high-elbow form.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-sky-900 min-w-[110px]">Single-arm</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">One arm at a time, other arm extended. Forces balance and a strong catch.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-sky-900 min-w-[110px]">6-kick switch</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Kick six times on your side, rotate, repeat. Trains body roll and rhythm.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Stroke shorthand -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white/50 backdrop-blur-sm p-4">
        <p class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-500 mb-3">Stroke shorthand</p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-4 gap-y-2.5 text-xs">
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Free</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Freestyle (front crawl). Default if no stroke is named.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">IM</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Individual Medley — fly, back, breast, free, in that order.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Kansas</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">A 300 in this order: 50 free, 50 back, 100 breast, 50 back, 50 free.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">Choice</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Pick your stroke — usually back or breast for recovery.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">@ 1:30</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">The interval — leave on this clock. Faster you swim, more rest you get.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="font-mono font-bold text-slate-700 min-w-[88px]">4 × 100</span>
            <span class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Four reps of 100 each. Total = 400. Reps × distance.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lane-divider mt-6"></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Sample workout preview -->
    <section class="mt-8" aria-label="Example workout">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-400">A real workout looks like this</p>
        <span class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-teal-600/70">example</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-teal-100 bg-white/70 backdrop-blur-sm p-4 sm:p-5">
        <div class="text-center mb-4 pb-3 border-b border-stone-200/70">
          <p class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900">Threshold Builder</p>
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-stone-500 mt-1">2,800 m · ~60 min · Pace: 1:45/100m · Endurance</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Warmup -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-l-amber-400 bg-amber-50/60 rounded-r-lg p-3 mb-2">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider bg-amber-500/90 text-white">Warmup</span>
            <span class="text-[11px] font-mono text-stone-400">600 m</span>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-1 text-[13px]">
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold min-w-[64px] text-right text-slate-700">400 m</span>
              <span class="flex-1 text-stone-600">easy free, smooth and loose</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold min-w-[64px] text-right text-slate-700">4 × 50 m</span>
              <span class="flex-1 text-stone-600">build by 25 — cruise, then strong</span>
              <span class="font-mono text-teal-600 text-[11px]">@ 1:00</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Pre-set -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-l-orange-400 bg-orange-50/60 rounded-r-lg p-3 mb-2">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider bg-orange-500/90 text-white">Pre-Set</span>
            <span class="text-[11px] font-mono text-stone-400">400 m</span>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-1 text-[13px]">
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold min-w-[64px] text-right text-slate-700">8 × 50 m</span>
              <span class="flex-1 text-stone-600 flex items-center gap-1.5 flex-wrap">
                kick — strong flutter, head down
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-800 px-2 py-0.5 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[9px]">Kick</span>
              </span>
              <span class="font-mono text-teal-600 text-[11px]">@ 1:15</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Main Set -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-l-teal-500 bg-teal-50/70 rounded-r-lg p-3 mb-2">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider bg-teal-600 text-white">Main Set</span>
            <span class="text-[11px] font-mono text-stone-400">1,600 m</span>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-1 text-[13px]">
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold min-w-[64px] text-right text-slate-700">4 × 200 m</span>
              <span class="flex-1 text-stone-600">free — descend 1→4, build effort each one</span>
              <span class="font-mono text-teal-600 text-[11px]">@ 3:30</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold min-w-[64px] text-right text-slate-700">8 × 100 m</span>
              <span class="flex-1 text-stone-600">free — hold threshold pace, even splits</span>
              <span class="font-mono text-teal-600 text-[11px]">@ 1:50</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Cooldown -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-l-cyan-400 bg-cyan-50/60 rounded-r-lg p-3">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider bg-cyan-500/90 text-white">Cooldown</span>
            <span class="text-[11px] font-mono text-stone-400">200 m</span>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-1 text-[13px]">
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono font-semibold min-w-[64px] text-right text-slate-700">200 m</span>
              <span class="flex-1 text-stone-600">choice — easy, breathe, shake out</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4 text-[11px] text-stone-400 text-center leading-relaxed">
          Your workout is generated fresh every time — different sets, intervals, and drills tuned to your duration and pace.
          Don't love what you got? Hit shuffle.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="lane-divider mt-6"></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Classic sets — swim history backbone -->
    <section class="mt-8" aria-label="Classic sets from swimming tradition">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3 gap-3 flex-wrap">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-400">Classic sets every pool deck knows</p>
        <span class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-teal-600/70">tradition</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The generator below builds something fresh each time, but every coach pulls from the same canon.
        Six sets that have stuck around — try one outright when you want a benchmark, or recognize them when they show up in your random workout.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        <!-- The Hour Swim -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-amber-900 text-sm leading-tight">The Hour Swim</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-amber-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">~ 3,000–6,000 m</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">Swim continuously for 60:00. Count yards.</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">A USMS national event since 1977 — the purest aerobic test there is. No intervals, no clock-watching beyond the wall, just one number at the end. Most lap swimmers fall between 3,000 and 4,500 yards; world records sit above 6,000.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- The Mile -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-sky-200 bg-sky-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-sky-900 text-sm leading-tight">The Mile</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-sky-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">1,650 y / 1,500 m</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">1 × 1650 free — for time.</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Pool swimming's standard distance event. Sub-25:00 is a fitness milestone; collegiate D-I cuts sit under 16:00. Negative-split it (second half faster than the first) and you'll have paced it right.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- 20 × 100 Free -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-teal-200 bg-teal-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-teal-900 text-sm leading-tight">The 20 × 100</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-teal-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">2,000 m · ~30 min</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">20 × 100 free @ 1:30 — hold the same time on every one.</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">The Masters main set. Drop the interval to find your aerobic threshold — the pace you can hold across all 20 with ~10 sec rest is your "T-pace," the number every distance coach builds around.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- 100 × 100s -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-rose-200 bg-rose-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-rose-900 text-sm leading-tight">The 100 × 100s</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-rose-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">10,000 y · ~3 hrs</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">100 × 100 free @ 1:30 — Christmas Day or New Year's morning.</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">A Masters tradition stretching back decades — clubs around the country gather on a holiday morning to grind through 10K yards as a group. The Olympic Club in San Francisco has hosted theirs every Christmas Eve since 1973. Equal parts ritual and rite of passage.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- 5 × 500 descend -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-orange-200 bg-orange-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-orange-900 text-sm leading-tight">5 × 500 Descend</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-orange-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">2,500 m · ~45 min</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">5 × 500 free @ 7:00 — descend 1→5 (each one faster than the last).</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">A Bob Bowman staple — the coach who built Phelps's distance base. The first 500 should feel almost lazy; the last is at threshold. Teaches pacing, patience, and how to find another gear when your arms don't want to.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Broken 200 -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-purple-200 bg-purple-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-purple-900 text-sm leading-tight">The Broken 200</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-purple-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">200 m · taper</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">4 × 50 race-pace, 10 sec rest between each. Add the splits — that's your projected 200.</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">The taper-week fixture. Lets you swim race-pace effort without race-pace fatigue. Add the four 50 splits and you have a credible prediction of next weekend's 200 — coaches set lineups around it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4 text-[11px] text-stone-400 text-center leading-relaxed">
        Want any of these built into a full warm-up / main / cooldown? Set the duration below and the generator will land near it.
      </p>

      <div class="lane-divider mt-6"></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Race events at a glance — what every workout points at -->
    <section class="mt-8" aria-label="Pool race events and what they train">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3 gap-3 flex-wrap">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-400">Race events at a glance</p>
        <span class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-teal-600/70">what training points at</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Every set you grind through is sized to a race somewhere. Six event groups make up almost all pool swimming —
        what each one tests, who's known for it, and where it shows up in your workout.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        <!-- The 50s -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-amber-900 text-sm leading-tight">The 50s</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-amber-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">~ 21–30 sec elite</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">50 free · 50 back · 50 breast · 50 fly</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Pure speed — almost no aerobic component. Won by underwaters, reactions, and stroke turnover. The 50 free crowns the fastest swimmer alive; Caeleb Dressel and Sarah Sjöström are the modern reference points. In your workout: <em>sprint sets at full rest</em>, build 25s, descending ladders.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- The 100s -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-teal-200 bg-teal-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-teal-900 text-sm leading-tight">The 100s</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-teal-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">~ :46–1:05 elite</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">100 free · 100 back · 100 breast · 100 fly</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">The marquee distance. 100 free is the prestige race of the meet; 100 fly was Phelps's signature. Half speed, half pain tolerance — the back fifty is where everything is decided. In your workout: <em>8 × 100 descending</em>, broken 100s, the 20 × 100 maps directly here.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- The 200s -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-sky-200 bg-sky-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-sky-900 text-sm leading-tight">The 200s</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-sky-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">~ 1:40–2:20 elite</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">200 free · 200 back · 200 breast · 200 fly · 200 IM</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Where pacing decides everything — long enough to need an engine, short enough that going out too hard ends you in the third 50. The 200 IM tests all four strokes in two minutes flat. In your workout: <em>5 × 200 descend</em>, broken 200s (the namesake), 4 × 50 race-pace add-the-splits.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Distance freestyle -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-purple-200 bg-purple-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-purple-900 text-sm leading-tight">Distance freestyle</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-purple-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">400 – 1,650</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">500 free (SCY) · 1,000 free · 1,650 / 1,500 free · 800 free</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Pure aerobic — won by whoever keeps form when their arms are done. The 1,500 LCM is "the mile," Katie Ledecky's terrain; sub-25:00 for the SCY mile is a fitness milestone, D-I cuts sit under 16:00. In your workout: <em>20 × 100 hold pace</em>, 5 × 500 descend, The Hour Swim.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- The IMs -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-rose-200 bg-rose-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-rose-900 text-sm leading-tight">The IMs</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-rose-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">all four strokes, one race</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">200 IM (50 of each) · 400 IM (100 of each)</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Fly → back → breast → free, every time. The 400 IM is nicknamed "The Beast" — Phelps's signature event because it punishes any weak stroke. The transitions matter more than the laps: lose the breast leg and the race is gone. In your workout: <em>kicked IMs, stroke-rotation pre-sets</em>, IM-order drill ladders.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- The relays -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-orange-200 bg-orange-50/50 p-4">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2 mb-1">
            <p class="font-bold text-orange-900 text-sm leading-tight">The relays</p>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-orange-700/70 whitespace-nowrap">team events · faster splits</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-mono text-[12px] text-stone-700 bg-white/60 rounded-md px-2.5 py-1.5 mt-2 mb-2">4 × 100 free · 4 × 100 medley · 4 × 200 free</p>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">The only events you swim for someone else. Flying-start splits run ~0.7 sec faster than open times — coaches build lineups around it: leadoff (steady), legs 2–3 (workhorses), anchor (the closer). Medley relays go back / breast / fly / free, each leg's specialist. In your workout: <em>flying-start 50s</em>, take-off practice, relay race-pace sets.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4 text-[11px] text-stone-400 text-center leading-relaxed">
        No race on the horizon? The same events still define your training — they're the units coaches build pace, rest, and progression around.
      </p>

      <div class="lane-divider mt-6"></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Pool etiquette — sharing the lane like you've been doing it for years -->
    <section class="mt-8" aria-label="Lane sharing and pool etiquette">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3 gap-3 flex-wrap">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-400">Sharing a lane without thinking about it</p>
        <span class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-teal-600/70">unwritten rules</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Lane etiquette is mostly invisible — until you violate it. Every regular pool runs on the same six conventions.
        Read these once and you'll fit in the first day, even at a pool you've never visited.
      </p>

      <!-- Top: lane choice diagram -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-teal-100 bg-white/70 backdrop-blur-sm p-4 sm:p-5 mb-3">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3">
          <p class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-teal-700/70">Pick the right lane</p>
          <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-stone-400">step one</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Most pools post pace signs but plenty don't. When in doubt, watch a 100 from each lane before you climb in — the right home picks itself.
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-2 text-[12px]">
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-amber-50 border border-amber-100 px-3 py-2.5">
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-1">
              <span class="font-bold text-amber-900">Slow lane</span>
              <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-amber-700/70">2:00+</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Recovery, drills, recreational laps. Often the wall lane — easier to pause at the side.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-teal-50 border border-teal-100 px-3 py-2.5">
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-1">
              <span class="font-bold text-teal-900">Medium lane</span>
              <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-teal-700/70">1:35–2:00</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Most regulars live here. Steady freestyle with the occasional set. The default if you're unsure.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-sky-50 border border-sky-100 px-3 py-2.5">
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-1">
              <span class="font-bold text-sky-900">Fast lane</span>
              <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-sky-700/70">sub-1:35</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 leading-snug">Masters, club swimmers, race pace work. Don't drop in for an easy 500 — pick the lane next door.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[11px] text-stone-400 leading-relaxed">
          Better to start one lane slow than one lane fast. You can always move up — moving down feels like a demotion.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Circle swim diagram -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-teal-100 bg-teal-50/40 backdrop-blur-sm p-4 sm:p-5 mb-3">
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3">
          <p class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-teal-700/70">Circle swim like driving</p>
          <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-stone-400">3+ swimmers</span>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-4 sm:gap-5 items-center">
          <!-- SVG diagram -->
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-white/70 border border-teal-100 p-3 mx-auto" style="width: 100%; max-width: 220px;">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 220 130" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Top-down view of a swim lane with arrows showing counter-clockwise circle swimming">
              <!-- lane outline -->
              <rect x="6" y="20" width="208" height="90" fill="#e0f2f1" stroke="#0d9488" stroke-width="1.5" rx="6"/>
              <!-- center dashed line -->
              <line x1="6" y1="65" x2="214" y2="65" stroke="#0d9488" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4 4" opacity="0.5"/>
              <!-- arrows: top half going right, bottom half going left -->
              <path d="M 30 42 L 90 42" stroke="#0d9488" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arr)"/>
              <path d="M 110 42 L 170 42" stroke="#0d9488" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arr)"/>
              <path d="M 190 88 L 130 88" stroke="#e11d48" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arr2)"/>
              <path d="M 110 88 L 50 88" stroke="#e11d48" stroke-width="2" fill="none" marker-end="url(#arr2)"/>
              <!-- swimmers as circles -->
              <circle cx="60" cy="42" r="5" fill="#0d9488"/>
              <circle cx="140" cy="42" r="5" fill="#0d9488"/>
              <circle cx="160" cy="88" r="5" fill="#e11d48"/>
              <circle cx="80" cy="88" r="5" fill="#e11d48"/>
              <!-- wall labels -->
              <text x="2" y="14" font-family="'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="9" fill="#64748b" font-weight="600">START WALL</text>
              <text x="170" y="125" font-family="'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif" font-size="9" fill="#64748b" font-weight="600">FAR WALL</text>
              <defs>
                <marker id="arr" viewBox="0 0 8 8" refX="6" refY="4" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto">
                  <path d="M 0 0 L 8 4 L 0 8 z" fill="#0d9488"/>
                </marker>
                <marker id="arr2" viewBox="0 0 8 8" refX="6" refY="4" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto">
                  <path d="M 0 0 L 8 4 L 0 8 z" fill="#e11d48"/>
                </marker>
              </defs>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-2">
              Three or more in a lane and you switch from <strong class="text-slate-800">splitting</strong> (each pick a side, swim straight up and down) to <strong class="text-slate-800">circle swimming</strong>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
              Stay <strong>right of the lane line</strong> in both directions — same as driving in the US. Out on the right, back on the right. The center line is the divider, not a target.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[11px] text-stone-400 italic leading-snug">
              Two swimmers? Splitting works fine — one takes each half. Add a third and everyone circles by silent agreement.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- The five rules grid -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-slate-700 text-white text-[9px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5">Rule 01</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-slate-800 text-[13px]">Ask before you join</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Hop down, catch the swimmer's eye on a flip, point at the lane and give a thumbs up. They'll nod and you slide in. No one says no — just don't drop in mid-set without the courtesy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-slate-700 text-white text-[9px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5">Rule 02</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-slate-800 text-[13px]">Tap the foot to pass</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Catching someone slower? <strong>One gentle tap on the toes</strong> on the second-to-last 25. They'll pull into the corner at the wall and let you go. Don't tap repeatedly — once is enough.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-slate-700 text-white text-[9px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5">Rule 03</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-slate-800 text-[13px]">Hug the corner at the wall</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Resting between sets? Stand or hang on the corner of the lane line, not the middle of the wall. Leaves the center clear for swimmers turning, and nobody pushes off into your face.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-slate-700 text-white text-[9px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5">Rule 04</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-slate-800 text-[13px]">Leave a 5-second gap</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Pushing off behind another swimmer? Wait <strong>five seconds</strong> on the wall. Anything closer and you're in their feet bubbles all 50 — bad for them, bad for you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-slate-700 text-white text-[9px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5">Rule 05</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-slate-800 text-[13px]">No backstroke surprises</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Backstroke in a shared lane? Glance over your shoulder every few strokes and aim down the line. Most lane collisions happen here — the swimmer going forward won't see you coming.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm p-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-slate-700 text-white text-[9px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-2 py-0.5">Rule 06</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-slate-800 text-[13px]">Gear stays in the corner</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[12px] text-stone-500 leading-snug">Pull buoy, fins, kickboard? Stack them on <strong>your half</strong> of the deck behind the lane, not floating in the lane. Floating gear gets kicked, lost, or in someone's face on the next push-off.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Closing line -->
      <p class="mt-4 text-[11px] text-stone-400 text-center leading-relaxed">
        None of this is in a rulebook — it's just how regulars share water. Do these and you'll be invisible in the best way: nobody notices you because nothing's out of place.
      </p>

      <div class="lane-divider mt-6"></div>
    </section>

    <!-- App -->
    <SwimWorkout client:idle />
  </main>

  <!-- Print target (React renders here too) -->
</BaseLayout>
